Q1/ What is the difference between a synchronized method and a synchronized block?

Answer:- Synchronized method provides either Object level class level lock.
         Synchronized block provides lock on any Object(specified in parameter);
         
         Synchronized method On entire functionality comparatively has greater scope.
         Synchronized block only limited to some statement comparatively has lesser scope.
         
         Synchronized method has lower performance.
         Synchronized block has the higher performance.
         
         
         Synchronized method blocks the entire class so any one can only use after other.
         Synchronized block only block the part that is required to be synchronized.
         
         
         
         
         
